<br>
The busy Tavern is filled with noise and laughter as those of the dark alliances revel in their victories of the day. As the night moves on the patrons become more loud and obnoxious. Balancing a tray with mugs of ale a small Teir’Dal female makes her way through the rowdy patrons. A young, male Warrior roughly grabs her arm as she places one of the mugs on the table.<br>
<br>
Turning eyes the color of ice, upon him she scowls, “Ye would do better not to touch me…. My Lord.” The last two words drip from her lips as sarcasm dipped in thick honey. All the males at the table laugh at the small girl and her pathetic threat. He releases her arm only to quickly grab her by the face pulling her eyes closer to his. Keeping his blood red eyes glaring directly into hers he shouts to the barkeep, “How much for the wench?!”<br>
<br>
“I am not a wench.” She growls out between clenched teeth. Her hand firmly on his arm she tries to free herself without spilling the mugs she holds with the other hand still on the tray. His eyes squint down to an evil smirk, “After tonight. We will see. You may even enjoy it.” She tosses her tray at him the ale spilling all over him and the floor. Still gripping her face tightly he stands, “You will pay for that wench.” Releasing her face he backhands her sending her sprawling to the floor.<br>
<br>
Strands of hair hang loosely in her face as she raises her cold eyes to meet his. She places her fingertip to her bleeding lip which heals itself upon her soft whisper. Suddenly, he grips her by the face once more pulling her to her feet. As she rises she deftly snatches a dagger from a nearby onlooker’s boot pressing it against the males neck, the only vulnerable place when fully armored. “Touch me and ye shall surely die.” She growls out at him.<br>
<br>
“Lithiah! That is not how we treat our patrons!” the barkeep shouts at her as he approaches.<br>
<br>
Ignoring the dagger she holds to his throat he holds her jaw firmly in his hand. Aware that one twist of his wrist would surely break her jaw she remains still but holds the dagger to his throat, still in defiance of him. His eyes never leaving hers he asks the barkeep again, now his voice even deeper and anger filled, “How much for the wench?”<br>
<br>
“She is not worthy to be a wench my Lord. Too young and inexperienced.” The barkeep says apologetically as he grabs another girl from a patrons lap. “Here, this one is pretty. She knows how to please a mighty warrior such as yourself.”<br>
<br>
“No.” He growls out, “This one. How much?” His eyes locked on hers she pushes the blade deeper into his skin. His face curls into a grin as blood begins trickling down his neck. “You will enjoy bleeding for me tonight, young one.” Unable to speak as his grip tightens on her jaw, a small whimper disobediently escapes her lips.<br>
<br>
“No, no my Lord. She is not worthy. Here, this one is pleasing.” The barkeep pleads. Finally, the Warrior glances over to the beautiful and much more well proportioned Teir’Dal female who flashes him a seductive smile. Returning his eyes to Lithiah he grins, “You have been lucky tonight. Go away little girl.” Tossing her aside he laughs quickly grabbing up the other girl placing her on his lap as he sits.<br>
<br>
The barkeep scowls, “Lithiah, follow me. NOW.” He takes the dagger from her hand and grabs her roughly by the arm providing a lecture her all the way back to the bar. Handing her another round of drinks, “Here, take these back and apologize. Or, I WILL let him have you tonight.”<br>
<br>
Lithiah nods silently, though the look of anger is still quite apparent on her face. She makes her way back to his table ignoring the pain remaining in her jaw. Placing the mugs on the table she looks over at the Warrior with cold eyes, “I….” She pauses a moment trying to spit out the words. “I….” Looking up at the barkeep she sees him watching her and looks back at the Warrior who looks up at her, quite amused with himself. <br>
<br>
An equally evil grin slides across her face as she coldly stares into his eyes, “I…. Pray to The Father…. That….” She leans down placing the tray onto the table, leaning close into his face. A wicked grin upon her blue Teir’Dal complexion. Their eyes lock with cold hatred towards each other, “I pray to The Father he allow me to take your life this night.”<br>
<br>
“Why you!” Tossing the wench aside he jumps up backhanding Lithiah to the floor once again. Scowling up at him from the floor she bolts as if a feline after prey as a deep growl erupts from her tiny body. From out of no where a foot deters her from her path finding it’s way to her ribs sending her flying sideways into a table. Quite dazed from her contact with the table she looks up to see a darkly dressed Shadow Knight facing the Warrior. His calm demeanor over the Warriors anger peaks her interest for only a moment before she stands ready to attack either of the two who come at her first.<br>
<br>
The Knight and Warriors eyes never leave each other as the Knight stretches his hand out to Lithiah. She looks at his hand for a moment, then to the two males facing each other. Feeling a strange sense of trust she places her hand in his and he pulls her behind him. “You will not touch my Charge. For, if you do. You touch death.” He says in a calm, but demanding, voice. The Warrior knowing this Knight is too much for him backs down causing a wicked grin to manifest from the Knights face.<br>
<br>
Still holding her hand the Knight turns dragging her along with him. Passing by the bar he tosses a bag of coins on the bar. “She’s not a wench mighty Knight” the barkeep says in more of a questioning tone than statement.<br>
<br>
“No. She is not. She is mine.” The Knight states calmly. The barkeep picks up the bag and feeling there is enough coin there to fully purchase 10 wenches he grins. “Do what you want with her. But, be warned. She has been nothing but trouble since she was found.”<br>
<br>
Grinning the Knight drags the girl behind him walking out the door, “Good. That’s what I had hoped.”<br>
