<br>
He turns grabbing her by the neck shoving her up against a wall. “Quiet or you die here.” Her eyes widen as he squeezes hard enough on her throat to just cut off the air. She tries in futility to remove his grasp as she pulls at his wrist to free her neck from his hand.<br>
<br>
He lets out a sigh of disappointment, “I thought you were stronger. I may be wrong.” Releasing her she slides down the wall holding her throat gasping for air. “Get up.” He states firmly as once again he roughly apprehends her arm dragging her along.<br>
<br>
Silently she follows him, more being dragged than walking on her own as his steps are fast but not running. “Where are we going?” she finally blurts out struggling to keep up with the Knight. “Quiet.” He says. She begins wondering what is to become of her when turning the last corner they come to a dead end.<br>
<br>
The Knight turns to face her. Holding her shoulders his eyes lock with hers, “Stay here. Do not take even one step.” His serious face weaves of an evil mixed grin. She nods silently then he is gone. She blinks a few times astonished at his disappearance.<br>
<br>
She rubs her still aching jaw as she looks around the alley. Walls of stone raise high into the night sky where she cannot see. She tries to peek around behind her trying not to move her feet as the Knight has instructed. Unable, she begins concentrating on the walls around her. Leaning a bit she peers at one part of a wall in particular. ‘Is it moving?’ she thinks to herself in silence.<br>
<br>
She straightens as whispers begin from all around her. The walls seem to be moving, shifting in her presence. She feels as if they touch her. Not her physical being. But, her inner soul. As the alley darkens she takes a ready stance, “Who are ye? What do ye want?”<br>
<br>
A whisper standing out before the others, that of the Knight, surrounds her as if entering into her mind and surrounding her body, “Who are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>you</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?” The question is stated to her in long drawn out words. “What do <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>you</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> want?”<br>
<br>
Her face turns cold, her voice angry, but the fear is apparent, “Don’t mock me. Answer me.” Her feet still unmoving she looks at the walls. Shifts as if rifts in time were more apparent now. Flickers from the stone seeming to be hands reaching out to her.<br>
<br>
“Answer <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>me</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.” The whisper states. Rising and fading as if a ripple in her mind. Her anger takes over as she growls lowly her foot shifting a bit with her hands raised in defense.<br>
<br>
She grins trying to bury the fear within her. Or, at least hide it. “Come on out Knight. I challenge ye.” An echo of laughter is heard encircling her. “You have your fathers resolve.”<br>
<br>
“My father? You are a Knight of Innoruuk and you don’t even call him your father?” she questions the whispering Knight. Her eyes continue watching the movement of the stone as forms of figures and doorways fade in and out.<br>
<br>
“I was hoping you would have your mothers ferocity. You may be too <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>weak</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.” The whisper of the Knight states calmly and directly into her mind. The word ‘weak’ emphasized to seek a reaction from her fulfills its Masters request.<br>
<br>
“I am not weak!” She shouts turning around thinking him behind her. As her foot leaves the ground she is kicked suddenly from a force she has never felt. She lands on the ground looking up, a deep growl departs her lips through angry clenched teeth. <br>
<br>
Snickers from thousands of directions aim directly into her mind. “Obey me. Now, rise and do not move unless told.”<br>
<br>
“No.” her voice defiant and strong she raises on her own terms. “I am not a slave.” When she straightens the force kicks her once more to the ground. A slight mutterance of a yelp escapes her as she lands back to the ground on all fours.<br>
<br>
“Lesson one. Do not ever refer to yourself as less than you are.” The whisper now sounding more real like. As if the person may actually be standing there. “We don’t have much time. Now, rise. And learn your next lesson.”<br>
<br>
Gathering her strength she stands in bold contempt, her body weak and pain filled. The night continues on, strike after strike as she continuously defies the shadowed Knight. <br>
<br>
Finally, when she is too weak to even stand the Knight appears before her. “I will not obey ye.” She growls out at him. Her words overflowing with anger and hatred for him. The pain within her body nearly unbearable.<br>
<br>
“Good.” He says causing her to look up at him with questioning eyes. The cold steel of his armored hand makes a loud clank as it meets her head.<br>
