“She wakes. Summon her Knight.” A low voice hisses a command. She tries to turn her head to the voice. But, again is left unmoving. <br>
<br>
“Get me off here.” She growls out at the darkness. Again she struggles against her own body to move. Just an inch would be an accomplishment.<br>
<br>
Hearing the clanking of heavy armor she hears the voice of the ShadowKnight once more. “Lay still Lithiah.” His voice, cold, demanding.<br>
<br>
“No!” she calls out towards him. “Let me go.” Again she struggles against herself.<br>
<br>
“Leave.” The voice of the ShadowKnight tells the others in the room. Hearing the feet of those in soft shoes scuffing on the floor tells they have left the room. But, she feels something. A sense of watching. Her mind tells her she is not alone. <br>
<br>
“Where are you?” she asks in an angry growl. “Release me and let me defend myself.” The ShadowKnight begins walking slowly around the altar where she lays. The shifting of his armor making soft clanks, his boots hitting the floor in sturdy steps. She even smells the scent of battle from him.<br>
<br>
“Lithiah, what was your first lesson?” he asks. His voice again, demanding an answer. Refusing to answer she growls low, trying to get her body to do something, anything. Just get one hand free even. Darkness remains about her as she struggles from within. “Answer.” He demands an answer giving her one last chance that she recklessly throws away.<br>
<br>
The ShadowKnight grins taking a dagger from his belt. Laying the flat of the blade across her bare stomach he asks one more time, “What was your first lesson?”<br>
<br>
Lithiah swallows hard, still unable to move, her mind panics. She growls in her only way to defend herself and struggles to move. The ShadowKnight tilts the blade causing its sharp edge to touch her skin. Her last warning to answer his question. Quieting her growl she spits out her words hatefully, “Never consider myself less than I am.”<br>
<br>
“Then…. Why are you still on the altar?” Though she cannot see him, the tone in his voice tells her he is enjoying this power over her and she growls angrily at him. She can hear he is amused as he snickers softly causing anger to rise within her. “What was the second lesson?”<br>
<br>
She calms herself, playing along with this game. What else could she do? Confused, she thinks back to the alley. Remember the taunts and punishments she spits out, “I will not obey ye.”<br>
<br>
“Almost correct.” He sneers out at her pushing the blade into her skin.<br>
<br>
Feeling the sting of her skin cutting once again she quickly states, “I will not obey.” <br>
<br>
Again he asks her, “Then….. Why are you still on the altar?” His voice menacing, taunting her causes a growl to well up in her throat that she tries to choke down.<br>
<br>
She blinks again. She can feel her eyes are open. She knows they are. But, nothing, its pitch black. Her mind torments her back to the alley. The moving wall, the grasping hands, the pain. She relives it once more her mind unable to suppress the fear and anger it raises within her. <br>
<br>
Pain sears through her body as she feels a hot substance poured over her feet. She tries to scream out being silenced with a large gag quickly shoved into her mouth. She can feel them pouring the hot substance up both her legs, the pain nearly sending her to unconsciousness. She begs in her mind to lose consciousness as the substance reaches her sensitive abdomen. <br>
<br>
Incantations fill her mind, whispers, voices, snickers, and laughter. Overwhelming her into another state of being. Still she can feel the pain of the hot substance keeping her senses peaked as it covers over her ribs slowly to her neck. An armored hand covers her mouth as the liquid is poured over her head. She panics at the air being cut off trying to inhale but is stopped by the firm grip of the hand, which could only belong to the ShadowKnight. Removing his hand, she pants against the gag in her mouth, the twisted cloth blocking some air. <br>
<br>
The heat from the liquid doesn’t fade as it seems to harden over her skin. She reels in this rapture of pain. Fear, hate, anguish all built up within her. Again she tries to scream feeling a blade of ice cut through the fiery dried substance into her skin. The blade goes deep into her skin, but avoids cutting into muscle. She pants again, the cloth now wet she rolls it with her tongue and pushes it down to breath. She hears the ShadowKnight mutter, “Good Lithiah. Fight for your life.”<br>
<br>
The carving of her skin with the blade of ice contrasted by the heat of the hard substance over her skin now seeming weak torture until they begin packing her wounds with a thick clay type substance which stings the sliced skin. Again she pants from the pain, the incantations of whispers, voices and sneering laughter rising in her head nearly deafening her. Finally she is released into unconsciousness<br>
